  "issue_title": "[bug] actuation: audit JSONL reads load entire file on every poll",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n\nActuation audit endpoints scan the **entire** append-only JSONL log even when callers only need the last N entries.\n\n`genie-core` (`actuation.rs` ~L341\u2013355): reads all lines into a `Vec`, then `drain`s to keep last N.\n\n`genie-api` (`routes.rs` ~L684\u2013690): `read_to_string` on the whole file, then `.lines().rev().take(50)`.\n\nOn a long-lived appliance, memory and latency grow linearly with log size on every dashboard poll.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Append thousands of lines to `data/safety/actuation-audit.jsonl`.\n2. Call actuation audit API or `read_recent_executed_actions`.\n3. Observe full-file read despite only returning last 32/50 entries.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTail-read only the last N lines; reject oversize single lines.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nFull file loaded into memory on every read.\n\n### Hardware\n\nx86 dev sufficient\n\n### JetPack / L4T version\n\n_No response_\n\n### GenieClaw version / commit\n\n`main` @ `crates/genie-core/src/tools/actuation.rs`, `crates/genie-api/src/routes.rs`\n\n### Relevant logs\n\n```\nN/A \u2014 degradation is gradual until log is large\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n**PR scope:** Shared tail reader + refactor core + API + multi-k-line tests (~100\u2013150 lines). Sized for \u22655 gittensor token score.\n\n**Duplicate check**\n\n| Item | Relation |\n|------|----------|\n| **#131** (open) | Audit write drops \u2014 different failure mode |\n| **#145** (closed) | Read IO error logging \u2014 not full-file scan |\n| **#24** (open, beta) | Broader audit epic |",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-27T22:42:40.000Z",
